28/06/2004
ISTANBUL, Turkey -- The NATO summit opened on Monday (28 June), gathering heads of state and government, defence and foreign ministers, and civilian and military officials from the 26 member states and 20 NATO partner countries. The summit is focusing on strengthening Alliance partnerships and on the situation in Iraq. Leaders agreed to help train Iraq's security forces in the face of increased attacks by insurgents. They also agreed to transfer the peacekeeping mission in Bosnia and Herzegovina to the EU at the end of the year. Outside the security zone surrounding the summit venue, police used tear gas against demonstrators, some of whom were armed with firebombs. (NATO Web site, Anadolu Agency, NTV, TRT 2, AFP, Reuters, CNN - 28/06/04)
